                    <history>
                        <origin notBefore="1490" notAfter="1490" cert="high" evidence="internal">
                            <p>Written in <origPlace>Denmark</origPlace> in <origDate when="1490">1490</origDate>, the Saturday after Pentecost.</p>
                            <p> Seven leaves, containing a calendar for Aarhus diocese, now
                                constituting <ref type="ms" target="#AM08-0169-en">169 8vo</ref>,
                                and two leaves two leaves containing annalistic notes, now
                                constituting <ref type="ms" target="#AM08-0233-en">AM 233 8vo</ref>,
                                were removed from this manuscript by <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name>. Yet the upper half of one
                                of the leaves is cut out and stuck to AM 10 8vo, apparently because
                                of the following message: 'Th<ex>en</ex>næ logbog hør p<ex>er</ex>
                                terckilsen <lb/>till í føwling oc lod he<ex>n</ex>næ siælff
                                <lb/>skriffæ aar æfft<ex>er</ex> gutz byrd M° <lb/>cdlxxx°
                                th<ex>e</ex>n løwerdag næsth <lb/>for pingetz dagh'.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The manuscript was owned by <name type="person" key="PerTer001">Per
                                Terkelsen</name> of Føvling, who also commisioned it.</p>
                        </provenance>
                    </history>
